# Parallel orchestration (Cursor)

Official references: [Cursor rules](https://cursor.com/docs/rules), [subagents](https://cursor.com/docs/subagents), [Agent Skills](https://cursor.com/docs/skills). Repository detail: `docs/agent-operational-reference.md` § Parallel orchestration.

## Parallelize when

- 2+ **independent** problems (different test files, subsystems, or root causes).
- Disjoint exploration (`engine/core` vs `engine/renderer` vs `editor/` vs one `games/<game>/`).
- Read-only audit/review while the parent implements or runs validation.
- CI log triage separate from local fix work.

## Stay sequential when

- The same file, migration, manifest fragment, schema, or public API family is being edited.
- Task B needs Task A output (design, types, ownership).
- Spec or module boundary is unresolved.

## Dispatch map (`Task`)

| Work | `subagent_type` | Role |
|------|-----------------|------|
| Codebase search / trace | `explore` | Evidence with paths and symbols |
| git / gh / CI shell work | `shell` | Repo `tools/*.ps1` wrappers; return logs |
| Isolated implementation | `generalPurpose` | Goal, Constraints, Done when in prompt |
| One failing check / lane | `ci-investigator` | One failure domain per agent |
| Coherent slice review | `code-reviewer` | After behavior is green |

- Launch **independent** subagents in **one parent message**.
- Use `run_in_background: true` for long independent work when Multitask Mode is on or the parent must coordinate.
- Prefer `.cursor/agents/*.md` roles when they match; otherwise use built-in `subagent_type` values above.
- Read-only roles stay `readonly: true`; only builder/fixer roles edit files.

## Parallel-safe boundaries

| Usually independent | Usually serialize |
|---------------------|-------------------|
| `engine/core/**`, `engine/platform/**`, `engine/renderer/**` | `engine/agent/manifest.fragments/**`, `schemas/**` |
| `editor/core/**` vs `editor/src/**` shell work | Root `CMakeLists.txt`, shared `tools/common.ps1` |
| One `games/<game>/**` lane | Same `.cpp` / `.hpp` translation unit |
| Disjoint `tools/check-*` investigations | `AGENTS.md` / rules / skills in one editing pass |

## Speed discipline

- Parent: decompose (`TodoWrite`), dispatch, synthesize, verify — do not redo subagent reads.
- Subagents: receive exact Goal, Context, Constraints, Done when; no parent chat history.
- Context: `tools/agent-context.ps1 -ContextProfile Minimal|Standard` and targeted manifest fragments.
- Validation: focused build/test/static loop first; one slice-close `tools/validate.ps1` (see `AGENTS.md`).

## Write isolation

Parallel **writes** need branch isolation: `git worktree add .worktrees/<name> -b <branch>`, then `tools/prepare-worktree.ps1` before configure. Read-only parallel dispatch does not require worktrees.

## Lifecycle

Consume subagent results, then close obsolete agents before spawning replacements. Synthesize evidence before claiming done.
